NOTE /SegmentIndex

                                            

                    
1
00:00:06.673 --> 00:00:07.674  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[explosion]

2
00:00:08.634 --> 00:00:09.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Report.

3
00:00:09.718 --> 00:00:11.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A ship just de-cloaked off
our port stern.

4
00:00:11.929 --> 00:00:14.223  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Can you identify them?
-They re-cloaked.

5
00:00:14.640 --> 00:00:16.016  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[explosion]

6
00:00:16.099 --> 00:00:18.227  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That disruptor blast
had a Klingon signature.

7
00:00:18.644 --> 00:00:20.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[beeps]

8
00:00:20.187 --> 00:00:22.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Evasive maneuvers. Hail them.

9
00:00:24.066 --> 00:00:25.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No response.

10
00:00:32.783 --> 00:00:35.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Port shields are down to 50 percent.

11
00:00:35.202 --> 00:00:36.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They've re-cloaked again.

12
00:00:36.828 --> 00:00:40.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The tetryon readings indicate
it's a D7-class cruiser.

13
00:00:40.624 --> 00:00:43.460  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
D7? They were retired decades ago.

14
00:00:44.169 --> 00:00:45.879  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Tuvok]
If their technology is antiquated...

15
00:00:45.963 --> 00:00:48.924  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Perhaps a metaphasic scan
might be able to penetrate their cloak.

16
00:00:49.841 --> 00:00:51.468  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do it.

17
00:00:51.552 --> 00:00:53.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bridge to Astrometrics.

18
00:00:53.095 --> 00:00:54.596  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Chakotay]
<i>Initiate a metaphasic sweep.</i>

19
00:00:57.975 --> 00:00:59.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've detected a vessel.

20
00:00:59.935 --> 00:01:01.895  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Transferring the trajectory to Tactical.

21
00:01:03.105 --> 00:01:04.231  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have them.

22
00:01:04.314 --> 00:01:05.399  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fire phasers.

23
00:01:12.072 --> 00:01:13.073  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Our cloak has failed.

24
00:01:13.699 --> 00:01:15.534  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Divert emergency power to shields.

25
00:01:16.660 --> 00:01:17.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[beeping]

26
00:01:17.744 --> 00:01:19.246  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Forward emitters are offline.

27
00:01:21.123 --> 00:01:23.875  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-The Federation ship is hailing again.
-Answer them.

28
00:01:23.959 --> 00:01:25.002  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain!

29
00:01:25.084 --> 00:01:27.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It may give us more time
to get the cloak back online.

30
00:01:27.754 --> 00:01:28.797  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Visual.

31
00:01:29.548 --> 00:01:33.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>This is Captain Kathryn Janeway</i>
<i>of the Federation Starship </i>Voyager.

32
00:01:33.969 --> 00:01:35.012  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Stand down.</i>

33
00:01:35.094 --> 00:01:38.348  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We will not surrender to sworn enemies
of the Klingon Empire.

34
00:03:29.960 --> 00:03:32.045  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Janeway]
I think there's been a misunderstanding.

35
00:03:32.129 --> 00:03:34.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Empire signed a peace treaty
with the Federation

36
00:03:34.506 --> 00:03:36.258  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
more than 80 years ago.

37
00:03:36.341 --> 00:03:38.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If I'm not mistaken, it's still in effect.

38
00:03:38.510 --> 00:03:39.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're lying.

39
00:03:40.178 --> 00:03:41.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>I'm not lying,</i>

40
00:03:42.055 --> 00:03:45.142  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>but even if I were,</i>
<i>your ship is no match for mine.</i>

41
00:03:46.226 --> 00:03:47.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>I suggest we discuss this.</i>

42
00:03:47.853 --> 00:03:49.020  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
What is there to talk about?

43
00:03:50.021 --> 00:03:51.565  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
The treaty, for one thing.

44
00:03:51.648 --> 00:03:54.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I'll give you access to our database
to show you I'm telling the truth.

45
00:03:55.068 --> 00:03:57.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Databases can be falsified.</i>

46
00:03:59.239 --> 00:04:01.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I have a Klingon
serving aboard this ship.

47
00:04:01.825 --> 00:04:03.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[Kohlar]
Impossible.

48
00:04:03.368 --> 00:04:04.619  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
She's my Chief Engineer.

49
00:04:05.579 --> 00:04:08.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I will meet this chief engineer.</i>

50
00:04:09.332 --> 00:04:11.710  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
We'd be honored to have you
as our guest.

51
00:04:17.257 --> 00:04:18.967  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You're safe here; you have my word.

52
00:04:19.050 --> 00:04:22.220  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Forgive me if I don't find the word
of a human very reassuring.

53
00:04:22.304 --> 00:04:24.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I'd like to know what you're doing
in the Delta Quadrant.

54
00:04:24.598 --> 00:04:27.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I'm not answering any questions
until I see the Klingon.

55
00:04:28.477 --> 00:04:30.061  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[beeping]

56
00:04:39.696 --> 00:04:40.739  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Captain Kohlar,

57
00:04:41.698 --> 00:04:44.576  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lieutenant Torres, our Chief Engineer.

58
00:04:46.703 --> 00:04:47.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You're with child.

59
00:04:49.247 --> 00:04:50.749  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's what the Doctor tells me.

60
00:04:51.541 --> 00:04:54.377  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Did you conceive
during the holy month of<i> nay'Poq?</i>

61
00:04:55.128 --> 00:04:56.588  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have no idea.

62
00:04:56.671 --> 00:04:58.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It would have been
14 or 15 weeks ago.

63
00:05:00.467 --> 00:05:03.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
That sounds about right,
not that it's any of your business.

64
00:05:05.013 --> 00:05:06.598  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I must return to my ship.

65
00:05:06.681 --> 00:05:08.683  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Aren't you interested
in learning about the treaty?

66
00:05:09.142 --> 00:05:10.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Here's a copy of the Khitomer Accords.

67
00:05:11.353 --> 00:05:12.896  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I must return to my vessel.

68
00:05:12.979 --> 00:05:16.066  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not without your assurance
that you won't fire on my ship again.

69
00:05:22.239 --> 00:05:23.406  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You have my word.

70
00:05:27.828 --> 00:05:30.914  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Escort Captain Kohlar
back to the Transporter Room.

71
00:05:31.331 --> 00:05:32.666  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aye, captain.

72
00:05:40.298 --> 00:05:41.883  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What the hell was that about?

73
00:05:43.718 --> 00:05:45.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Klingons clamoring]

74
00:05:45.095 --> 00:05:46.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's the truth.

75
00:05:46.930 --> 00:05:48.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How can you be certain?

76
00:05:48.974 --> 00:05:50.475  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Scrolls say:

77
00:05:50.559 --> 00:05:53.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"You will find me after two warring houses
make peace."

78
00:05:54.813 --> 00:06:00.735  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Our people and the Federation,
our greatest enemy are at peace.

79
00:06:00.819 --> 00:06:03.196  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So the humans claim.

80
00:06:03.864 --> 00:06:06.116  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
These Accords may be a deception.

81
00:06:06.199 --> 00:06:07.576  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The other signs are present.

82
00:06:08.451 --> 00:06:11.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"You will know me
before I know the world."

83
00:06:12.497 --> 00:06:14.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The child is unborn.

84
00:06:14.583 --> 00:06:16.585  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It does not know the world.

85
00:06:16.668 --> 00:06:18.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You interpret the Scrolls well.

86
00:06:19.087 --> 00:06:21.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We must verify the evidence.

87
00:06:21.840 --> 00:06:24.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your skepticism
darkens my heart, T'Greth.

88
00:06:25.010 --> 00:06:28.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What evidence did our ancestors have
when they began this journey?

89
00:06:28.805 --> 00:06:30.849  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nothing but their faith.

90
00:06:30.932 --> 00:06:32.100  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[murmuring]

91
00:06:32.183 --> 00:06:33.935  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell the others to prepare.

92
00:06:34.811 --> 00:06:38.023  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Day of Separation has arrived.

93
00:06:38.106 --> 00:06:40.442  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Klingons murmuring]

94
00:06:46.448 --> 00:06:47.949  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[alarm bleeping]

95
00:06:48.033 --> 00:06:50.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Captain, the Klingon ship--
Its core is breaching.

96
00:06:50.952 --> 00:06:52.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Red Alert. Hail them.

97
00:06:53.663 --> 00:06:55.081  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I salute you, captain.</i>

98
00:06:56.583 --> 00:06:59.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You did more damage to our vessel</i>
<i>than my engineer thought.</i>

99
00:07:00.587 --> 00:07:01.755  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can send over a team

100
00:07:01.838 --> 00:07:03.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to help you establish
a containment field.

101
00:07:03.757 --> 00:07:05.467  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>-There isn't time.</i>
-[Kim] He's right.

102
00:07:05.884 --> 00:07:07.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Their core is going to breach
in less than 30 seconds.

103
00:07:07.969 --> 00:07:09.971  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I'm requesting emergency transport.</i>

104
00:07:10.680 --> 00:07:13.725  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain, their crew complement is 204.

105
00:07:17.228 --> 00:07:18.229  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

106
00:07:18.313 --> 00:07:20.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Erect force fields around
the Shuttle Bay. Transport them there.

107
00:07:21.775 --> 00:07:24.027  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Tell your crew to stand by
for evacuation.

108
00:07:24.486 --> 00:07:25.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ten seconds.

109
00:07:25.737 --> 00:07:27.572  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If we're still too close
when their core breaches...

110
00:07:27.656 --> 00:07:29.532  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Go to warp
as soon as their crew is aboard.

111
00:07:31.076 --> 00:07:34.079  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Five, four, three...

112
00:07:35.080 --> 00:07:36.081  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We have them.

113
00:07:42.045 --> 00:07:45.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[loud buzz of conversation]

114
00:07:53.807 --> 00:07:55.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You spared us a dishonorable death.

115
00:07:56.017 --> 00:07:57.060  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sensor logs indicate

116
00:07:57.143 --> 00:08:00.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that the containment failure
was not caused by our weapons.

117
00:08:00.271 --> 00:08:02.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You activated a self-destruct sequence.

118
00:08:03.441 --> 00:08:05.944  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It was the only way
to get us aboard<i> Voyager.</i>

119
00:08:06.027 --> 00:08:07.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why was that so important?

120
00:08:07.779 --> 00:08:10.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's our sacred duty to be here.

121
00:08:12.242 --> 00:08:13.410  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't understand.

122
00:08:15.078 --> 00:08:16.663  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
More than 100 years ago,

123
00:08:17.414 --> 00:08:19.916  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
my great-grandfather was part of a sect

124
00:08:20.375 --> 00:08:22.877  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
which believed
the Empire had lost its way.

125
00:08:23.878 --> 00:08:25.588  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They discovered a sacred text.

126
00:08:26.256 --> 00:08:30.844  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It told them to embark on a journey
to a distant region of the galaxy.

127
00:08:31.469 --> 00:08:34.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You've been traveling
for four generations?

128
00:08:34.347 --> 00:08:39.144  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My people have always known
the voyage would be long and difficult,

129
00:08:40.395 --> 00:08:42.814  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but the Scrolls said
we would be rewarded.

130
00:08:44.065 --> 00:08:45.442  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How?

131
00:08:45.942 --> 00:08:50.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We would find the<i> kuvah'magh,</i>
the savior of our people,

132
00:08:50.572 --> 00:08:52.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the one who will lead us
to a new Empire.

133
00:08:53.908 --> 00:08:57.245  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Scrolls instruct us
to follow her wherever she goes.

134
00:08:57.704 --> 00:09:00.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What does any of this have to do
with<i> Voyager?</i>

135
00:09:01.207 --> 00:09:03.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I believe the<i> kuvah'magh</i>

136
00:09:03.918 --> 00:09:07.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
is the unborn child of B'Elanna Torres.

137
00:09:07.881 --> 00:09:08.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're joking.

138
00:09:10.216 --> 00:09:12.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They take their beliefs very seriously.

139
00:09:13.303 --> 00:09:15.930  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Seriously enough
to destroy their own ship?

140
00:09:16.014 --> 00:09:18.016  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Couldn't they have just followed us?

141
00:09:18.099 --> 00:09:23.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Apparently, their sacred text
told them to cast off the old ways

142
00:09:23.271 --> 00:09:25.857  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
as soon as they found this<i> kuvah'magh.</i>

143
00:09:25.940 --> 00:09:29.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They saw their vessel
as the last vestige of the corrupt Empire.

144
00:09:29.652 --> 00:09:31.321  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was hoping our daughter
would be special,

145
00:09:31.404 --> 00:09:33.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I never dreamed
she'd turn out to be the Klingon messiah.

146
00:09:33.907 --> 00:09:35.116  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This isn't funny.

147
00:09:35.909 --> 00:09:38.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They might be dangerous.
What if they want to hurt the baby?

148
00:09:38.536 --> 00:09:39.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
To them, your baby's sacred.

149
00:09:39.788 --> 00:09:41.873  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's unlikely they would do anything
to harm her.

150
00:09:41.956 --> 00:09:44.751  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Two hundred Klingons pose
a significant security threat.

151
00:09:44.834 --> 00:09:46.795  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I suggest we keep them confined
to the Shuttle Bay

152
00:09:46.878 --> 00:09:48.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
until we can find a
suitable home for them.

153
00:09:48.922 --> 00:09:50.465  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There are women and children
down there.

154
00:09:50.548 --> 00:09:51.883  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can't just lock them up.

155
00:09:51.966 --> 00:09:53.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I agree.
-Captain.

156
00:09:53.259 --> 00:09:55.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Assign extra security to every deck,

157
00:09:55.386 --> 00:09:58.932  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and make sure the Klingons know
and abide by the rules.

158
00:09:59.015 --> 00:10:01.768  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Bridge will have to be off limits.
Engineering as well.

159
00:10:01.851 --> 00:10:03.478  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Keep them out of all restricted areas.

160
00:10:03.895 --> 00:10:06.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Despite their reverence
for Lieutenant Torres,

161
00:10:06.106 --> 00:10:08.316  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
she should be assigned
a 24-hour security detail.

162
00:10:08.733 --> 00:10:09.734  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just what I need.

163
00:10:09.818 --> 00:10:11.694  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where are they going to sleep?

164
00:10:12.779 --> 00:10:14.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll double up in quarters.

165
00:10:14.364 --> 00:10:15.865  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll ask for volunteers.

166
00:10:16.282 --> 00:10:17.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know this isn't going to be easy,

167
00:10:17.742 --> 00:10:19.494  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but until we can find
another place for them,

168
00:10:19.577 --> 00:10:21.663  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we should do our best
to make them feel comfortable.

169
00:10:21.746 --> 00:10:22.956  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dismissed.

170
00:10:34.008 --> 00:10:36.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[buzz of conversation]

171
00:10:41.641 --> 00:10:44.018  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain, you must try the<i> gagh.</i>

172
00:10:44.102 --> 00:10:45.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll pass, thank you,

173
00:10:46.020 --> 00:10:48.398  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I'm glad to see
you're getting into the spirit of things.

174
00:10:48.481 --> 00:10:50.567  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I've been studying
the Klingon database.

175
00:10:50.650 --> 00:10:54.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They're a fascinating people;
very robust,

176
00:10:54.237 --> 00:10:58.533  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and, uh, they certainly seem
to appreciate my culinary skills.

177
00:10:58.616 --> 00:11:00.702  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It looks like everything's
running smoothly.

178
00:11:00.785 --> 00:11:03.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh, not quite everything.

179
00:11:04.080 --> 00:11:07.876  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Some of the Starfleet people
have been complaining

180
00:11:07.959 --> 00:11:09.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
about the smell.

181
00:11:10.128 --> 00:11:12.005  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Personally, I find it appealing.

182
00:11:12.088 --> 00:11:13.089  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sniffs]

183
00:11:13.173 --> 00:11:15.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A kind of musky aroma.

184
00:11:15.258 --> 00:11:17.385  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe we can adjust
the environmental controls

185
00:11:17.468 --> 00:11:19.179  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to filter out the musk.

186
00:11:19.262 --> 00:11:21.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thief!

187
00:11:21.306 --> 00:11:24.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Touch my food again,
and I'll kill you!

188
00:11:24.267 --> 00:11:27.604  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Okay, everybody relax.
-[Klingon] He took<i> gagh </i>from my plate.

189
00:11:27.686 --> 00:11:31.149  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you don't mind, Ensign,
I've been studying Klingon etiquette.

190
00:11:31.232 --> 00:11:33.318  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You shouldn't quarrel over food.

191
00:11:33.401 --> 00:11:36.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Save your strength for battle,
to fight those who would challenge you.

192
00:11:37.322 --> 00:11:38.740  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[growling]

193
00:11:38.823 --> 00:11:40.074  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Kim]
Take it easy!

194
00:11:40.158 --> 00:11:41.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting and growling]

195
00:11:42.452 --> 00:11:43.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's enough!

196
00:11:44.662 --> 00:11:46.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You have a fiery spirit.

197
00:11:47.582 --> 00:11:48.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

198
00:11:48.666 --> 00:11:50.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You will make a worthy mate.

199
00:11:53.421 --> 00:11:54.505  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What a day!

200
00:11:55.882 --> 00:11:59.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groaning and grunting]

201
00:12:00.845 --> 00:12:04.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I never met a more
ravenous group in my life.

202
00:12:04.682 --> 00:12:08.061  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I must have served over 300 meals.

203
00:12:08.144 --> 00:12:10.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mr. Neelix, may I ask
what you're doing here?

204
00:12:12.273 --> 00:12:13.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're bunkmates.

205
00:12:14.692 --> 00:12:16.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There must be some mistake.

206
00:12:16.277 --> 00:12:19.072  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[laughing]
No, there's no mistake.

207
00:12:19.155 --> 00:12:21.491  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I gave up my quarters
to a Klingon family.

208
00:12:22.158 --> 00:12:24.244  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
By the time I checked
with Commander Chakotay,

209
00:12:24.327 --> 00:12:26.287  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you were the only one
who hadn't been paired up.

210
00:12:26.955 --> 00:12:28.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You should've consulted me.

211
00:12:29.624 --> 00:12:32.794  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're such close friends,
I knew you wouldn't mind.

212
00:12:33.670 --> 00:12:38.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mr. Neelix,
as much as I enjoy your company,

213
00:12:38.466 --> 00:12:40.385  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I prefer solitude in my own quarters.

214
00:12:42.053 --> 00:12:45.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You don't really want me to go back there
and tell that family to get out, do you?

215
00:12:49.686 --> 00:12:54.691  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Good, because I promise you
we're going to have fun, Mr. Vulcan.

216
00:12:54.773 --> 00:12:56.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckling]

217
00:12:56.401 --> 00:12:59.153  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I learned some Klingon drinking songs.

218
00:12:59.237 --> 00:13:01.656  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[belongings clatter to floor]

219
00:13:02.115 --> 00:13:03.241  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll teach them to you.

220
00:13:03.741 --> 00:13:06.828  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Ej IM-ta fey DE-ja i</i>

221
00:13:06.911 --> 00:13:10.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>ejdahk-so-TAS</i>
<i>ghos va Skral byteek</i>

222
00:13:10.373 --> 00:13:13.084  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Ej IM-ta fey DE-ja i...</i>

223
00:13:13.710 --> 00:13:14.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Paris to Torres.</i>

224
00:13:14.919 --> 00:13:16.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm almost finished.

225
00:13:16.212 --> 00:13:17.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Paris]
<i>You said that an hour ago.</i>

226
00:13:17.755 --> 00:13:20.675  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll be there in a minute, I promise.
Torres out.

227
00:13:20.758 --> 00:13:23.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Keep an eye on the replicators.
They've already gone down once today.

228
00:13:25.847 --> 00:13:26.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's her!

229
00:13:30.226 --> 00:13:31.227  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

230
00:13:40.028 --> 00:13:42.363  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When you said, "Be there in a minute,"
you weren't kidding.

231
00:13:42.447 --> 00:13:46.034  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A group of Klingons ambushed me
outside of Engineering.

232
00:13:46.117 --> 00:13:47.702  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I decided transporting myself

233
00:13:47.785 --> 00:13:49.828  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
would be easier
than running the gauntlet.

234
00:13:51.664 --> 00:13:53.624  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm starting to feel like a prisoner.

235
00:13:54.250 --> 00:13:57.128  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, at least you have
a handsome cell mate.

236
00:13:57.628 --> 00:13:59.630  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How long do you think they're going
to be on board?

237
00:14:00.381 --> 00:14:03.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought you'd be glad
to have other Klingons around.

238
00:14:04.177 --> 00:14:05.178  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've always told me

239
00:14:05.261 --> 00:14:07.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
how uncomfortable it is
being the only one.

240
00:14:07.555 --> 00:14:09.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I guess I should be careful
what I wish for.

241
00:14:09.932 --> 00:14:12.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe you should talk to some of them,
give them a chance.

242
00:14:12.602 --> 00:14:13.603  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door chimes]

243
00:14:13.686 --> 00:14:14.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come in.

244
00:14:17.357 --> 00:14:19.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Captain.
-Sorry to bother you but I need your help.

245
00:14:20.735 --> 00:14:22.945  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ten of the Klingons
have started a hunger strike.

246
00:14:23.029 --> 00:14:26.115  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They say they won't eat until you agree
to meet with their Council of Elders.

247
00:14:26.199 --> 00:14:27.408  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's ridiculous.

248
00:14:27.492 --> 00:14:29.702  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Their faith is obviously
very important to them.

249
00:14:29.786 --> 00:14:31.788  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They think I'm something I'm not.

250
00:14:31.871 --> 00:14:34.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Just talk to them,
hear what they have to say.

251
00:14:36.417 --> 00:14:38.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We could be with these people
for a while.

252
00:14:38.252 --> 00:14:39.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You can't avoid them forever.

253
00:14:40.004 --> 00:14:41.089  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can try.

254
00:14:41.798 --> 00:14:44.258  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If it'll make you feel any better,
I'll go with you.

255
00:14:48.471 --> 00:14:51.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>mobaR, DoH'lo maj, Qo-vuh'makh.</i>

256
00:14:51.724 --> 00:14:54.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>mobaR, DoH'lo maj, Qo-vuh'makh.</i>

257
00:14:54.894 --> 00:14:58.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>mobaR, DoH'lo maj, Qo-vuh'makh.</i>

258
00:14:58.106 --> 00:15:01.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>mobaR, DoH'lo maj, Qo-vuh'makh.</i>

259
00:15:01.234 --> 00:15:04.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>mobaR, DoH'lo maj, Qo-vuh'makh.</i>

260
00:15:04.487 --> 00:15:07.573  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>mobaR, DoH'lo maj, Qo-vuh'makh.</i>

261
00:15:07.657 --> 00:15:10.201  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>mobaR, DoH'lo maj, Qo-vuh'makh.</i>

262
00:15:10.785 --> 00:15:12.078  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>mobaR...</i>

263
00:15:13.871 --> 00:15:15.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You honor us with your presence.

264
00:15:18.709 --> 00:15:19.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look at her ridges.

265
00:15:21.212 --> 00:15:22.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Morak was right.

266
00:15:23.548 --> 00:15:25.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your blood is not pure.

267
00:15:26.551 --> 00:15:27.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

268
00:15:27.969 --> 00:15:29.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My father was human.

269
00:15:30.012 --> 00:15:31.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[murmuring]

270
00:15:32.140 --> 00:15:33.891  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Couldn't you see this for yourself?

271
00:15:34.767 --> 00:15:36.477  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Yes, but--
-Why didn't you tell us?!

272
00:15:36.561 --> 00:15:37.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It wasn't important!

273
00:15:38.771 --> 00:15:40.064  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not important?

274
00:15:42.358 --> 00:15:44.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We destroyed our ship

275
00:15:44.277 --> 00:15:47.071  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
because you said she was the mother
of the<i> kuvah'magh.</i>

276
00:15:47.155 --> 00:15:49.031  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Show me where it's written

277
00:15:49.115 --> 00:15:52.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that the<i> kuvah'magh</i>
must have pure Klingon blood.

278
00:15:52.368 --> 00:15:56.122  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The prophecy wouldn't lead us
to a mongrel child.

279
00:15:56.205 --> 00:15:58.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, take it easy.

280
00:15:58.291 --> 00:15:59.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who are you?

281
00:16:00.001 --> 00:16:02.462  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The father of that "mongrel" child.

282
00:16:03.963 --> 00:16:06.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
More human blood.

283
00:16:06.174 --> 00:16:09.135  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your<i> kuvah'magh</i>
isn't even half Klingon.

284
00:16:09.218 --> 00:16:12.054  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've spent my life
interpreting the Scrolls,

285
00:16:12.138 --> 00:16:15.266  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I say that all the signs
of the prophecy are here.

286
00:16:15.975 --> 00:16:16.976  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Liar.

287
00:16:18.561 --> 00:16:20.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've led us to a false savior.

288
00:16:31.949 --> 00:16:33.367  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I told you this was a mistake.

289
00:16:33.451 --> 00:16:36.078  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lieutenant, I need your help.

290
00:16:36.162 --> 00:16:37.288  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Any more help from me,

291
00:16:37.371 --> 00:16:38.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and you're going to have a holy war
on your hands.

292
00:16:38.998 --> 00:16:41.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's what I'm trying to prevent.

293
00:16:48.591 --> 00:16:51.302  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My baby's just a baby.

294
00:16:51.385 --> 00:16:52.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's not a savior.

295
00:16:52.970 --> 00:16:54.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Perhaps you're right,

296
00:16:54.222 --> 00:16:56.807  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but we <i>must</i> convince
my people that she is.

297
00:16:56.891 --> 00:16:57.892  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why?

298
00:16:59.060 --> 00:17:01.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've traveled more
than 30,000 light-years

299
00:17:01.479 --> 00:17:03.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in search of this savior,

300
00:17:03.856 --> 00:17:07.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and in more than 100 years,
we've found nothing

301
00:17:07.360 --> 00:17:09.946  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
except hardship and isolation.

302
00:17:11.447 --> 00:17:13.824  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When I saw Lieutenant Torres,

303
00:17:13.908 --> 00:17:15.660  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that she was with child

304
00:17:16.285 --> 00:17:20.873  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I didn't know if I was looking
at the mother of the<i> kuvah'magh</i> or not,

305
00:17:20.957 --> 00:17:23.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I did know I was looking
at an opportunity

306
00:17:23.376 --> 00:17:24.877  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to end this wasteful journey.

307
00:17:25.795 --> 00:17:27.630  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then you don't believe in the prophecy?

308
00:17:27.713 --> 00:17:30.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What I believe is that my people
have suffered enough.

309
00:17:31.259 --> 00:17:33.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If they accept your child
as the<i> kuvah'magh,</i>

310
00:17:34.053 --> 00:17:36.055  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you'll hold great influence over them.

311
00:17:36.931 --> 00:17:38.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can find a suitable planet.

312
00:17:38.391 --> 00:17:41.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You can tell them it's their new home,
and they'll follow you there.

313
00:17:42.603 --> 00:17:44.230  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not going to lie to them.

314
00:17:44.814 --> 00:17:45.940  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's the alternative?

315
00:17:46.899 --> 00:17:50.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My people staying aboard your ship,
draining your resources?

316
00:17:50.736 --> 00:17:52.238  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I agree with Lieutenant Torres.

317
00:17:52.321 --> 00:17:54.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm not comfortable
deceiving your people.

318
00:17:54.949 --> 00:17:57.910  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Perhaps you won't have to lie to them
to convince them.

319
00:17:57.994 --> 00:17:59.078  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you suggesting?

320
00:18:00.079 --> 00:18:02.707  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If you study the Scrolls with me,

321
00:18:02.790 --> 00:18:05.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we may be able to interpret them
in a way that appears

322
00:18:05.418 --> 00:18:07.837  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
consistent with the events of your life.

323
00:18:07.920 --> 00:18:11.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then we'll bring those consistencies
to the attention of the Council.

324
00:18:13.092 --> 00:18:16.429  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So you just want to stretch
the truth a little?

325
00:18:17.013 --> 00:18:22.643  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It is possible that the Sacred Scrolls
were scrawled by a madman in a cave,

326
00:18:22.727 --> 00:18:25.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or perhaps they really
were divinely inspired.

327
00:18:25.605 --> 00:18:29.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Either way, they've guided us
for over a century.

328
00:18:29.483 --> 00:18:31.819  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If my people start to believe

329
00:18:31.902 --> 00:18:34.447  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that the Sacred Scrolls
have led them astray,

330
00:18:35.531 --> 00:18:36.782  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
there may be violence.

331
00:18:37.783 --> 00:18:38.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is that a threat?

332
00:18:39.452 --> 00:18:40.995  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Merely a fact.

333
00:18:42.413 --> 00:18:45.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're doing everything you can
to get your people home, captain.

334
00:18:46.792 --> 00:18:49.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's all I'm doing for mine.

335
00:18:54.175 --> 00:18:58.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It says, "The<i> kuvah'magh</i> will be
descended from a noble house."

336
00:19:00.514 --> 00:19:02.058  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't come from one,

337
00:19:02.141 --> 00:19:03.976  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I'm pretty sure
my husband doesn't either.

338
00:19:04.810 --> 00:19:08.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We all have nobility in our blood,
if we go back far enough.

339
00:19:08.773 --> 00:19:11.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So these Scrolls can mean
anything you want them to.

340
00:19:12.318 --> 00:19:16.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It is written that the mother
of the<i> kuvah'magh</i>

341
00:19:16.447 --> 00:19:17.782  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
would be an off-worlder.

342
00:19:19.075 --> 00:19:21.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Weren't you born
on a Federation colony?

343
00:19:21.202 --> 00:19:22.995  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A lot of Klingons are born off-world.

344
00:19:23.079 --> 00:19:26.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It also says that you would've
lived a life of solitude

345
00:19:26.791 --> 00:19:28.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and endured many hardships.

346
00:19:29.460 --> 00:19:30.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's accurate, isn't it?

347
00:19:32.963 --> 00:19:34.048  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
According to this,

348
00:19:35.883 --> 00:19:38.135  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"I'm supposed to have won
a glorious victory

349
00:19:38.219 --> 00:19:40.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
against an army of 10,000 warriors."

350
00:19:40.221 --> 00:19:41.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Haven't you?

351
00:19:41.764 --> 00:19:45.393  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We haven't even encountered
10,000 warriors.

352
00:19:45.476 --> 00:19:47.061  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, unless you include the Borg.

353
00:19:47.645 --> 00:19:49.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Did you help destroy
one of their vessels?

354
00:19:51.649 --> 00:19:52.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I suppose.

355
00:19:52.733 --> 00:19:55.111  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Couldn't that have been
your glorious victory?

356
00:19:55.611 --> 00:19:56.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I guess so.

357
00:19:59.281 --> 00:20:00.866  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where are the images of Kahless?

358
00:20:02.868 --> 00:20:04.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where is your family crest?

359
00:20:05.788 --> 00:20:07.081  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They clashed with the carpet.

360
00:20:09.208 --> 00:20:11.752  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't you honor
any of your people's traditions?

361
00:20:12.962 --> 00:20:13.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not really.

362
00:20:14.922 --> 00:20:17.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There is one tradition
we can honor together.

363
00:20:22.179 --> 00:20:23.556  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you doing?

364
00:20:24.390 --> 00:20:25.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's midday.

365
00:20:26.267 --> 00:20:29.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Time to remember the sacrifice
of our ancestors.

366
00:20:30.688 --> 00:20:32.857  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Haven't you made
a Plea for the Dead before?

367
00:20:33.357 --> 00:20:35.109  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, not since I was a child.

368
00:20:35.192 --> 00:20:37.403  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The dead can't rest in<i> Sto-Vo-Kor</i>

369
00:20:38.362 --> 00:20:40.614  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
if the living don't honor their memory.

370
00:20:43.909 --> 00:20:47.413  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Perhaps there's someone
I can honor on your behalf.

371
00:20:48.122 --> 00:20:50.082  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who did you plead for as a child?

372
00:20:51.083 --> 00:20:52.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My grandmother.

373
00:20:52.877 --> 00:20:53.878  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She was called?

374
00:20:55.045 --> 00:20:56.046  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
L'Naan.

375
00:21:00.843 --> 00:21:01.844  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kahless...

376
00:21:03.179 --> 00:21:06.056  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We implore you
to remember those warriors

377
00:21:07.183 --> 00:21:08.768  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
who have fallen in your name.

378
00:21:10.644 --> 00:21:13.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lift them out of the cavern of despair

379
00:21:15.441 --> 00:21:17.401  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and reveal yourself to them

380
00:21:19.153 --> 00:21:20.446  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in all your glory.

381
00:21:20.529 --> 00:21:21.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right, "in all your glory."

382
00:21:22.907 --> 00:21:26.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Remember Kolax, son of Amar.

383
00:21:27.870 --> 00:21:29.038  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Remember Talij,

384
00:21:30.706 --> 00:21:33.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
daughter of K'Rene.

385
00:21:36.879 --> 00:21:37.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Remember L'Naan,

386
00:21:40.049 --> 00:21:41.217  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
daughter of Krelik.

387
00:21:57.399 --> 00:21:58.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What happened to you?

388
00:21:58.984 --> 00:22:00.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I cut myself shaving.

389
00:22:01.570 --> 00:22:04.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Is that a bite mark?
-One of the Klingons attacked me.

390
00:22:04.949 --> 00:22:08.410  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Did you do something to provoke him?
-Not him, her.

391
00:22:08.494 --> 00:22:11.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And she wasn't provoked,
she was aroused.

392
00:22:11.956 --> 00:22:14.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah. I'm not surprised.

393
00:22:14.792 --> 00:22:16.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've studied the section
on Klingon mating rituals

394
00:22:16.919 --> 00:22:18.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in their cultural database.

395
00:22:18.754 --> 00:22:21.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then maybe you can tell me
how to convince a female twice my size

396
00:22:21.966 --> 00:22:23.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that I'm not interested.

397
00:22:23.342 --> 00:22:26.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Hmm, you probably can't.
-Great.

398
00:22:26.178 --> 00:22:27.638  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As I understand it,

399
00:22:27.721 --> 00:22:30.266  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you have two options, kill her

400
00:22:31.392 --> 00:22:32.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
or mate with her.

401
00:22:33.477 --> 00:22:35.896  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Since the first option
is clearly unacceptable...

402
00:22:35.980 --> 00:22:36.981  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's this?

403
00:22:37.064 --> 00:22:39.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Authorization for you
to engage in intimate relations

404
00:22:39.191 --> 00:22:40.943  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
with a member of an alien species.

405
00:22:41.026 --> 00:22:42.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Be sure to get the captain's
approval as well.

406
00:22:44.655 --> 00:22:49.243  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Chief Engineer's Personal Log,</i>
<i>Stardate 54518.2.</i>

407
00:22:49.326 --> 00:22:52.246  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I've spent the last two days</i>
<i>reviewing the Sacred Scrolls</i>

408
00:22:52.329 --> 00:22:55.249  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>in preparation for my appearance</i>
<i>before the Klingon Council.</i>

409
00:22:55.332 --> 00:22:58.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Kohlar also suggested I prepare</i>
<i>a few "colorful stories"</i>

410
00:22:59.003 --> 00:23:00.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>to help win them over.</i>

411
00:23:00.588 --> 00:23:04.382  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's when they beamed
aboard the<i> Flyer, </i>weapons firing.

412
00:23:04.466 --> 00:23:08.012  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Tuvok and Neelix fought valiantly,
but there were too many Hirogen.

413
00:23:08.095 --> 00:23:13.851  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I had to face ten
of their fiercest hunters alone.

414
00:23:14.935 --> 00:23:16.812  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[B'Elanna] I--
-Is that how<i> you</i> remember it?

415
00:23:16.896 --> 00:23:20.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Exaggeration is part of Klingon custom.

416
00:23:20.357 --> 00:23:21.525  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's doing great.

417
00:23:21.609 --> 00:23:23.903  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
...were shot out of my hand,
forcing me to take down

418
00:23:23.986 --> 00:23:27.489  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
the last hunter in hand-to-hand combat.

419
00:23:27.573 --> 00:23:29.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It was a glorious fight.

420
00:23:29.909 --> 00:23:32.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your ancestors would be honored.

421
00:23:33.996 --> 00:23:35.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[metal cups clinking]

422
00:23:39.209 --> 00:23:41.003  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You tell a good story,

423
00:23:42.004 --> 00:23:43.839  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but that's not why you're here.

424
00:23:44.632 --> 00:23:48.928  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Some say you are the mother
of the<i> kuvah'magh,</i>

425
00:23:49.511 --> 00:23:52.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the one who will guide us
to a new homeworld.

426
00:23:52.848 --> 00:23:56.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Has your unborn child
told you where it is?

427
00:23:56.602 --> 00:23:58.312  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughter]

428
00:24:02.066 --> 00:24:03.567  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Scrolls say,

429
00:24:04.610 --> 00:24:08.989  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"You will follow in my footsteps
before I have made them."

430
00:24:11.449 --> 00:24:13.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yesterday, we changed course

431
00:24:13.869 --> 00:24:16.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
toward a planet very much like Qo'noS.

432
00:24:18.207 --> 00:24:19.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, in a manner of speaking,

433
00:24:20.960 --> 00:24:24.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you are now following my child
to a new home.

434
00:24:24.964 --> 00:24:26.464  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[murmuring]

435
00:24:26.548 --> 00:24:28.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You deliver the words we want to hear,

436
00:24:28.759 --> 00:24:31.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but it's Kohlar who gives them to you.

437
00:24:32.179 --> 00:24:34.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are you his puppet
in the bedchamber as well?

438
00:24:35.516 --> 00:24:37.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Watch it.
That's my wife you're talking about.

439
00:24:38.476 --> 00:24:39.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He speaks!

440
00:24:40.020 --> 00:24:41.355  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I didn't think you had a tongue.

441
00:24:41.855 --> 00:24:43.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Leave him out of this.

442
00:24:43.399 --> 00:24:46.318  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You see how he hides
behind his female?

443
00:24:47.820 --> 00:24:51.657  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It is also written that the father
of the<i> kuvah'magh</i>

444
00:24:51.740 --> 00:24:53.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
will be an honorable warrior.

445
00:24:55.119 --> 00:24:58.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Would an honorable warrior
ever refuse a challenge?

446
00:24:59.039 --> 00:25:01.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I haven't refused any challenge.

447
00:25:02.626 --> 00:25:04.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I haven't made one yet.

448
00:25:09.507 --> 00:25:10.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You and I...

449
00:25:14.388 --> 00:25:15.639  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
To the death.

450
00:25:17.725 --> 00:25:19.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Tom...
-Stay out of this.

451
00:25:22.187 --> 00:25:23.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[T'Greth]
<i>Pahtk.</i>

452
00:25:29.903 --> 00:25:31.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I accept.

453
00:25:31.238 --> 00:25:32.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[boisterous approval]

454
00:25:34.033 --> 00:25:36.076  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[cups clinking]

455
00:25:41.957 --> 00:25:44.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[Paris] What was I supposed to say?
-How about "no"?

456
00:25:44.460 --> 00:25:45.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They were all watching.

457
00:25:46.003 --> 00:25:47.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There would have been a riot
if I refused.

458
00:25:47.713 --> 00:25:50.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-So, you're going to get yourself killed?
-What makes you so sure I'd lose?

459
00:25:51.050 --> 00:25:52.051  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, please.

460
00:25:52.134 --> 00:25:55.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Look, I have no intention
of fighting anyone to the death,

461
00:25:55.387 --> 00:25:57.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but wasn't the whole point of this
to get them to believe

462
00:25:57.973 --> 00:25:59.557  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that we<i> are</i> the parents of their savior?

463
00:25:59.641 --> 00:26:01.559  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Captain, this has gone too far.
Put a stop to it.

464
00:26:02.144 --> 00:26:03.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I intend to.

465
00:26:03.937 --> 00:26:04.938  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tuvok.

466
00:26:05.022 --> 00:26:06.564  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door opens]

467
00:26:10.652 --> 00:26:11.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Gentlemen...

468
00:26:12.863 --> 00:26:15.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm afraid Lieutenant Paris
had no authority to accept this challenge.

469
00:26:16.075 --> 00:26:18.619  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There will be no death matches
aboard my ship.

470
00:26:18.702 --> 00:26:22.081  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I told you this<i> pahtk</i>
was not the true father.

471
00:26:22.164 --> 00:26:25.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Lieutenant Paris is perfectly willing
to fight you, Mr. T'Greth.

472
00:26:25.334 --> 00:26:27.795  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm the one preventing him
from doing so.

473
00:26:27.878 --> 00:26:32.674  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The father of the<i> kuvah'magh</i>
wouldn't let a woman speak for him.

474
00:26:33.884 --> 00:26:34.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
T'Greth...

475
00:26:36.136 --> 00:26:38.555  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There is precedent
for an honorable compromise.

476
00:26:40.265 --> 00:26:43.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A nonlethal bout,
fought with blunted<i> bat'leths.</i>

477
00:26:43.894 --> 00:26:45.729  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The victory goes to the first warrior

478
00:26:45.813 --> 00:26:48.357  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to knock his opponent
to the ground three times.

479
00:26:48.440 --> 00:26:49.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A coward's rules!

480
00:26:49.566 --> 00:26:51.735  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Was the Emperor Mur'Eq a coward?

481
00:26:52.361 --> 00:26:54.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He was the one
who instituted these rules

482
00:26:54.571 --> 00:26:58.450  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to insure that his warriors would kill
their enemies and not each other.

483
00:27:00.536 --> 00:27:02.371  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If you agree to these terms

484
00:27:03.789 --> 00:27:05.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll allow the match.

485
00:27:07.376 --> 00:27:10.254  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll see you on the field of battle!

486
00:27:15.509 --> 00:27:18.762  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I assume you have a suitable holodeck
training program for this, Lieutenant?

487
00:27:20.638 --> 00:27:23.517  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He'll be ready. I'll train him myself.

488
00:27:29.606 --> 00:27:30.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door opens]

489
00:27:32.151 --> 00:27:33.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hi.

490
00:27:34.945 --> 00:27:36.029  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Psst! Neelix.

491
00:27:38.574 --> 00:27:40.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Something wrong, Harry?
-Shh!

492
00:27:40.284 --> 00:27:41.910  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Have you seen her?
-Who?

493
00:27:41.994 --> 00:27:44.246  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh, that Klingon woman.

494
00:27:44.329 --> 00:27:46.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The one I got into a scrape with
in the Mess Hall.

495
00:27:46.582 --> 00:27:48.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Officer Ch'Rega.

496
00:27:48.292 --> 00:27:49.626  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's her.

497
00:27:49.710 --> 00:27:51.003  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I haven't seen her today.

498
00:27:51.545 --> 00:27:53.338  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's been following me everywhere.

499
00:27:53.422 --> 00:27:54.506  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why?

500
00:27:54.590 --> 00:27:56.216  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She wants to mate.

501
00:27:56.300 --> 00:27:59.052  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh! You're a lucky man.

502
00:27:59.136 --> 00:28:01.513  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She's a fine specimen
of Klingon womanhood.

503
00:28:02.139 --> 00:28:04.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I guess it's a matter of taste.
You never saw me!

504
00:28:05.517 --> 00:28:07.561  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, wait!

505
00:28:07.644 --> 00:28:10.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I have a better idea.
-Neelix, what the hell are you doing?

506
00:28:10.105 --> 00:28:12.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Play along.
I'm taking her off your hands.

507
00:28:13.442 --> 00:28:14.860  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When I say you're limited

508
00:28:14.943 --> 00:28:17.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to two servings of<i> brak't,</i>
that's all you get!

509
00:28:17.237 --> 00:28:18.655  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you understand me, Ensign?

510
00:28:19.239 --> 00:28:22.201  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Yes, sir, whatever you say.
-I don't think you do.

511
00:28:22.868 --> 00:28:25.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If I catch you eating
more than your share again,

512
00:28:25.287 --> 00:28:26.872  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll cut it out of your belly.

513
00:28:27.998 --> 00:28:29.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>-What?</i>
-[whispers] Run.

514
00:28:31.043 --> 00:28:32.753  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Excuse me.
<i>-Pahtk.</i>

515
00:28:38.717 --> 00:28:40.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[growling]

516
00:28:52.314 --> 00:28:54.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I didn't think you approved
of this kind of competition.

517
00:28:54.733 --> 00:28:57.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't. I'm here in an official capacity.

518
00:28:58.028 --> 00:29:00.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, you do know they're fighting
with nonlethal weapons?

519
00:29:00.489 --> 00:29:03.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You'd be surprised how much damage
a blunt<i> bat'leth</i> can do.

520
00:29:04.534 --> 00:29:06.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Warriors, assemble!

521
00:29:09.790 --> 00:29:12.751  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Today would be a very bad day to die.

522
00:29:12.834 --> 00:29:14.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll try to remember that.

523
00:29:18.423 --> 00:29:20.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let honor guide you!

524
00:29:21.426 --> 00:29:22.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Tagh!</i>

525
00:29:28.100 --> 00:29:31.478  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I see fear in your eyes, human.

526
00:29:32.104 --> 00:29:35.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The only Klingon I'm afraid of is my wife
after she's worked a double shift.

527
00:29:36.858 --> 00:29:38.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[both grunting]

528
00:29:56.086 --> 00:29:58.630  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[both gruntling]

529
00:30:26.616 --> 00:30:28.493  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groans weakly]

530
00:30:30.162 --> 00:30:32.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[wheezing]

531
00:30:58.106 --> 00:30:59.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's begun.

532
00:31:00.067 --> 00:31:01.401  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you talking about?

533
00:31:01.485 --> 00:31:02.486  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's dying.

534
00:31:04.321 --> 00:31:06.907  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Typically, I'm the one to make
that kind of prognosis.

535
00:31:06.990 --> 00:31:08.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's the<i> nehret.</i>

536
00:31:08.700 --> 00:31:09.701  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It kills all of us

537
00:31:09.785 --> 00:31:11.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
who aren't fortunate enough
to die in battle.

538
00:31:18.543 --> 00:31:21.004  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[doctor]
It's a retrovirus that destroys the cells

539
00:31:21.088 --> 00:31:23.340  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
by attacking
the cytoplasmic membranes.

540
00:31:23.423 --> 00:31:25.300  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shouldn't our bio-filters have detected it

541
00:31:25.384 --> 00:31:27.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
when we transported
the Klingons aboard?

542
00:31:27.427 --> 00:31:28.762  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is an insidious virus.

543
00:31:28.845 --> 00:31:30.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It lies dormant,

544
00:31:30.305 --> 00:31:32.891  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
disguising itself
as inert genetic material

545
00:31:32.974 --> 00:31:35.519  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
until it inexplicably activates.

546
00:31:36.395 --> 00:31:38.522  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The<i> nehret</i> always comes
without warning.

547
00:31:39.398 --> 00:31:41.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've reviewed my scans
of the other Klingons.

548
00:31:42.150 --> 00:31:43.443  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're all carriers.

549
00:31:45.946 --> 00:31:48.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why didn't you tell us
your people had a disease?

550
00:31:48.698 --> 00:31:51.284  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've never thought of it as a disease.

551
00:31:51.368 --> 00:31:54.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's more like old age.

552
00:31:54.413 --> 00:31:55.414  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is it contagious?

553
00:31:56.873 --> 00:31:57.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Only to Klingons.

554
00:32:04.172 --> 00:32:07.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you'd give us some privacy,
I'd like to examine Lieutenant Torres.

555
00:32:08.510 --> 00:32:09.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Of course.

556
00:32:29.197 --> 00:32:30.365  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The baby, too?

557
00:32:31.867 --> 00:32:33.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm afraid so.

558
00:32:37.831 --> 00:32:38.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why am I here?

559
00:32:41.418 --> 00:32:42.419  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're ill.

560
00:32:43.003 --> 00:32:44.754  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You collapsed during the fight.

561
00:32:46.923 --> 00:32:48.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The<i> nehret.</i>

562
00:32:48.425 --> 00:32:49.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

563
00:32:50.218 --> 00:32:52.053  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you for telling us.

564
00:32:52.137 --> 00:32:53.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now my baby and I have it, too.

565
00:32:57.851 --> 00:32:59.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where do you think you're going?

566
00:32:59.811 --> 00:33:03.023  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
To prepare for my journey
to<i> Sto-Vo-Kor.</i>

567
00:33:03.106 --> 00:33:04.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You should be in Sick Bay.

568
00:33:04.816 --> 00:33:06.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can you make me well?

569
00:33:06.902 --> 00:33:10.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Not at the moment, but--
-Then don't deny me my tradition.

570
00:33:14.493 --> 00:33:16.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[guttural tonal droning]

571
00:33:28.715 --> 00:33:32.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The child is not the<i> kuvah'magh.</i>

572
00:33:33.178 --> 00:33:35.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But the father accepted your challenge.

573
00:33:35.597 --> 00:33:37.098  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He defeated you!

574
00:33:37.182 --> 00:33:39.476  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was defeated by the<i> nehret!</i>

575
00:33:41.895 --> 00:33:46.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
B'Elanna Torres<i> and</i> her child
will fall victim to it as well.

576
00:33:47.359 --> 00:33:48.568  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Impossible!

577
00:33:48.652 --> 00:33:50.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They both carry it.

578
00:33:50.904 --> 00:33:52.239  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She told me herself.

579
00:33:53.114 --> 00:33:56.701  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But the Scrolls say the<i> kuvah'magh</i>
is younger than old age.

580
00:33:57.160 --> 00:33:59.955  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And stronger than sickness.

581
00:34:01.081 --> 00:34:03.041  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She cannot be our savior.

582
00:34:03.667 --> 00:34:05.043  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[murmuring]

583
00:34:05.710 --> 00:34:07.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We should resume our search.

584
00:34:08.463 --> 00:34:11.216  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Kohlar and many
of the others won't agree.

585
00:34:11.299 --> 00:34:13.134  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then we must act alone!

586
00:34:14.844 --> 00:34:16.555  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
For the good of our people.

587
00:34:18.890 --> 00:34:19.891  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How?

588
00:34:21.393 --> 00:34:23.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll wait for the right moment.

589
00:34:25.146 --> 00:34:26.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And when it comes...

590
00:34:27.816 --> 00:34:29.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
...we'll seize<i> Voyager!</i>

591
00:34:30.068 --> 00:34:32.070  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[approving growls]

592
00:34:40.829 --> 00:34:42.914  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've identified
two potential colony sites

593
00:34:42.998 --> 00:34:44.416  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in the southern hemisphere.

594
00:34:44.499 --> 00:34:47.168  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll require topographical scans.

595
00:34:47.252 --> 00:34:48.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll prepare them.

596
00:34:51.840 --> 00:34:53.258  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I shouldn't have doubted you.

597
00:34:55.719 --> 00:34:57.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It appears the signs
were there all along.

598
00:35:00.265 --> 00:35:02.058  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll join the survey mission.

599
00:35:03.268 --> 00:35:04.394  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're ill, old friend.

600
00:35:05.729 --> 00:35:06.771  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You should remain here.

601
00:35:08.773 --> 00:35:13.111  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want my final days
to be spent in honorable pursuits.

602
00:35:13.903 --> 00:35:16.740  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't ask me to die inside these walls.

603
00:35:20.035 --> 00:35:21.620  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We transport in one hour.

604
00:35:35.884 --> 00:35:39.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your transporters are much
more sophisticated than ours.

605
00:35:39.179 --> 00:35:41.056  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've studied Klingon transport systems.

606
00:35:41.139 --> 00:35:43.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The basic technology
isn't all that different.

607
00:35:43.516 --> 00:35:47.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But you were able to beam our entire crew
aboard<i> Voyager </i>at one time.

608
00:35:47.354 --> 00:35:49.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We usually don't like to do that
for safety reasons,

609
00:35:49.731 --> 00:35:52.567  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but in a pinch,
we can expand the buffer capacity.

610
00:35:53.526 --> 00:35:55.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-These are the targeting scanners?
-Exactly.

611
00:35:56.071 --> 00:35:57.864  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They work
on the same principles as yours.

612
00:36:05.288 --> 00:36:06.289  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You said it was urgent?

613
00:36:06.373 --> 00:36:09.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I need to conduct
a more detailed bio-scan of your baby.

614
00:36:09.376 --> 00:36:10.585  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's not sick, is she?

615
00:36:10.669 --> 00:36:12.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, but I may be onto something.

616
00:36:14.756 --> 00:36:17.008  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be leading the team going to Site A.

617
00:36:17.092 --> 00:36:19.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Kohlar will be in charge
of the Site B team.

618
00:36:20.261 --> 00:36:21.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Morning, Commander. Harry.

619
00:36:23.431 --> 00:36:25.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

620
00:36:26.184 --> 00:36:27.894  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groans]

621
00:36:31.481 --> 00:36:32.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[alarm bleeping]

622
00:36:32.565 --> 00:36:34.442  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Phaser fire in Transporter Room 1.

623
00:36:35.694 --> 00:36:36.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bridge to Chakotay.

624
00:36:52.127 --> 00:36:54.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-They're on the surface.
-Now lock on to the Bridge officers.

625
00:36:56.673 --> 00:36:59.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They've activated a force field
around Deck 1.

626
00:36:59.342 --> 00:37:01.469  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Transport the rest of their crew.

627
00:37:02.804 --> 00:37:05.348  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Captain, I'm detecting
multiple transports.

628
00:37:05.432 --> 00:37:07.684  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Some of our people
are being beamed down to the surface.

629
00:37:07.767 --> 00:37:09.352  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Cut power to the transporters.

630
00:37:11.688 --> 00:37:12.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't.

631
00:37:12.939 --> 00:37:13.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bridge to Engineering.

632
00:37:15.275 --> 00:37:17.068  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
B'Elanna, respond.

633
00:37:18.445 --> 00:37:19.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's no one in Engineering.

634
00:37:24.451 --> 00:37:27.787  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-The Bridge officers?
-I still can't get a lock.

635
00:37:27.871 --> 00:37:29.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[frustrated grunt]

636
00:37:29.330 --> 00:37:32.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can you transport us there?

637
00:37:32.083 --> 00:37:33.084  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll try.

638
00:37:41.426 --> 00:37:43.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Computer,
open the Transporter Room doors.

639
00:37:43.678 --> 00:37:45.764  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Security override:
Tuvok-pi-alpha.

640
00:38:26.805 --> 00:38:28.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Grant me a warrior's death.

641
00:38:31.976 --> 00:38:33.186  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I beg of you.

642
00:38:33.812 --> 00:38:37.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sorry. No mercy killings on my Bridge.

643
00:38:40.485 --> 00:38:41.486  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get our people back.

644
00:38:42.904 --> 00:38:44.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, ma'am.

645
00:39:00.713 --> 00:39:03.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why am I not in<i> Sto-Vo-Kor?</i>

646
00:39:03.424 --> 00:39:05.134  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Because you are healthy as a<i> targ.</i>

647
00:39:07.303 --> 00:39:09.806  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-The<i> nehret?</i>
-Gone.

648
00:39:10.348 --> 00:39:13.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have B'Elanna Torres' child
to thank for it.

649
00:39:15.228 --> 00:39:17.146  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The fetus has hybrid stem cells.

650
00:39:17.230 --> 00:39:19.732  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They contain Klingon and human DNA.

651
00:39:19.816 --> 00:39:21.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I used them to synthesize an antivirus.

652
00:39:23.111 --> 00:39:26.030  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The child cured me?

653
00:39:26.114 --> 00:39:27.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was the one
who devised the treatment.

654
00:39:28.074 --> 00:39:29.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Doctor...

655
00:39:29.492 --> 00:39:31.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, of course, the child cured you.

656
00:39:32.453 --> 00:39:35.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The<i> kuvah'magh </i>has healed all of us.

657
00:39:36.207 --> 00:39:39.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She truly is our savior.

658
00:39:49.012 --> 00:39:52.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Captain's Log, Stardate 54529.8.</i>

659
00:39:52.849 --> 00:39:54.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>While we're helping the Klingons</i>
<i>into their new home,</i>

660
00:39:55.018 --> 00:39:58.396  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>life aboard</i> Voyager
<i>is gradually returning to normal.</i>

661
00:40:01.316 --> 00:40:03.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Computer, open this door.

662
00:40:03.568 --> 00:40:06.195  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Access to these quarters</i>
<i>has been restricted.</i>

663
00:40:06.279 --> 00:40:08.031  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
On whose authority?

664
00:40:08.114 --> 00:40:09.115  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Neelix.</i>

665
00:40:09.657 --> 00:40:11.534  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Neelix, open this door.

666
00:40:12.285 --> 00:40:13.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be there in a minute, Commander.

667
00:40:14.454 --> 00:40:16.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's<i> my</i> boot.

668
00:40:16.122 --> 00:40:19.125  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Computer, security override.
Authorization: Tuvok-pi...

669
00:40:24.339 --> 00:40:27.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Goodbye, my little<i> par'machkai.</i>
-Goodbye, my fearless warrior.

670
00:40:28.009 --> 00:40:30.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh!

671
00:40:30.178 --> 00:40:32.555  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[growling]

672
00:40:40.396 --> 00:40:41.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm really going to miss her.

673
00:40:54.911 --> 00:40:55.912  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ohh.

674
00:40:57.705 --> 00:40:58.706  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[clanking]

675
00:41:00.833 --> 00:41:02.377  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't you worry, Mr. Vulcan.

676
00:41:02.794 --> 00:41:04.212  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[nervous laugh]

677
00:41:05.213 --> 00:41:07.632  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll have this place

678
00:41:07.715 --> 00:41:09.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
shipshape in no time at all.

679
00:41:10.969 --> 00:41:11.970  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chortles]

680
00:41:12.053 --> 00:41:14.597  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just go, Mr. Neelix.

681
00:41:23.439 --> 00:41:24.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's this?

682
00:41:24.524 --> 00:41:27.235  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The<i> bat'leth </i>given to me
by my great-grandfather.

683
00:41:28.319 --> 00:41:29.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's for your daughter.

684
00:41:31.531 --> 00:41:34.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I hope someday you'll tell her about us.

685
00:41:37.036 --> 00:41:38.162  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will.

686
00:41:48.631 --> 00:41:50.842  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Qapla',</i> B'Elanna Torres.

687
00:41:52.301 --> 00:41:53.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Qapla'.</i>

688
00:42:02.854 --> 00:42:05.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It doesn't seem right
just to hang it on the wall.

689
00:42:05.732 --> 00:42:08.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm not letting you
scratch it up on the holodeck.

690
00:42:09.485 --> 00:42:12.321  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sure our daughter
wouldn't mind lending it to the old man

691
00:42:12.405 --> 00:42:13.406  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
every now and then.

692
00:42:15.450 --> 00:42:19.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, this is one special kid
we're going to have.

693
00:42:19.412 --> 00:42:21.289  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're just figuring that out?

694
00:42:22.415 --> 00:42:25.501  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I was hoping for an artist,
or maybe a musician.

695
00:42:26.753 --> 00:42:30.131  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But she's already the savior
of an entire race.

696
00:42:31.549 --> 00:42:33.217  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You don't really believe that.

697
00:42:33.718 --> 00:42:34.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know.

698
00:42:34.802 --> 00:42:36.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There are a lot
of coincidences to explain.

699
00:42:37.722 --> 00:42:40.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I mean, what were the odds
that they'd run into the one ship

700
00:42:40.391 --> 00:42:42.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
in the whole Quadrant
with a Klingon aboard?

701
00:42:43.102 --> 00:42:45.813  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Probably about the same odds
that you and I would get married.

702
00:42:48.232 --> 00:42:51.694  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe we should name her
<i>kuvah'magh...</i>

703
00:42:51.778 --> 00:42:52.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just to be safe.

704
00:42:57.492 --> 00:42:58.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Put it on the list.

